00:30:00,300 --> 00:30:02,100
Hey, Senior.

557
00:30:09,400 --> 00:30:10,700
Was he really that strong?

558
00:30:10,700 --> 00:30:14,800
He was the best spiker for two years in a row.

559
00:30:14,800 --> 00:30:16,700
Let's go!

560
00:30:21,700 --> 00:30:23,000
This--

561
00:30:24,100 --> 00:30:25,499
Why did you help cover for me?

562
00:30:25,499 --> 00:30:26,999
The manager has to protect his teammates.

563
00:30:26,999 --> 00:30:29,800
Did you think you wouldn't get hurt yourself?

564
00:30:29,800 --> 00:30:31,876
Anyway, I can't get on the court and play,

565
00:30:31,876 --> 00:30:33,980
so it doesn't make any difference to me.

566
00:30:52,200 --> 00:30:55,200
What kind of injury would produce such a big scar?

567
00:31:10,900 --> 00:31:13,100
No wonder he can't play volleyball.

568
00:31:19,900 --> 00:31:20,900
Fuck.

569
00:31:20,900 --> 00:31:22,800
What am I doing?

570
00:31:33,000 --> 00:31:36,400
Everyone is working hard for this goal.

571
00:31:36,400 --> 00:31:39,600
This is also the last opportunity for He Cheng En and myself.

572
00:31:42,600 --> 00:31:44,000
What kind of goal is that?

573
00:31:44,000 --> 00:31:46,600
Why was he trying to act cool?

574
00:32:02,200 --> 00:32:04,000
Let's begin.

575
00:32:05,900 --> 00:32:08,620
Remember to switch partners when you reach the blue line.

576
00:32:17,000 --> 00:32:18,100
He Cheng En.

577
00:32:18,100 --> 00:32:19,100
Stop slacking off.

578
00:32:19,100 --> 00:32:23,000
Continue. The captain should lead the team.

579
00:32:24,600 --> 00:32:26,500
No.

580
00:32:26,500 --> 00:32:29,700
This exercise postion is so ugly; it's not cool at all.

581
00:32:29,700 --> 00:32:32,520
Strength or looking cool: Which is more important?

582
00:32:33,900 --> 00:32:35,900
Looking cool, of course.

583
00:32:36,700 --> 00:32:38,499
Captain's team, do another twenty sets.

584
00:32:38,500 --> 00:32:40,100
Back and forth.

585
00:32:40,100 --> 00:32:42,200
All right!

586
00:32:42,200 --> 00:32:44,076
You're not that cruel, are you?

587
00:32:44,076 --> 00:32:46,000
Without changing partners.

588
00:32:48,000 --> 00:32:50,020
Carry on! Do you guys also want to do more?

589
00:32:50,020 --> 00:32:52,000
Get on with it.

590
00:32:57,600 --> 00:32:58,700
Continue!

591
00:32:58,700 --> 00:33:01,700
Hey! You finally appeared.

592
00:33:01,700 --> 00:33:03,600
Why are you here?

593
00:33:07,000 --> 00:33:09,000
I'm here to practice.

594
00:33:09,000 --> 00:33:11,100
Very good.

595
00:33:11,100 --> 00:33:14,000
Yes, very good.

596
00:33:15,100 --> 00:33:17,500
Come, you and Da Ke are a group.

597
00:33:17,500 --> 00:33:20,200
Cheng En, you're taking him.

598
00:33:20,200 --> 00:33:20,900
Me?

599
00:33:20,900 --> 00:33:21,800
Yes.

600
00:33:21,800 --> 00:33:23,400
Hang on, does that mean...

601
00:33:23,400 --> 00:33:26,100
Yes, twenty rounds.

602
00:33:26,100 --> 00:33:28,000
Follow him. Twenty sets.

603
00:33:28,000 --> 00:33:30,400
I'll be tired to death. Are you even human?

604
00:33:30,400 --> 00:33:31,001
Go on!

605
00:33:31,001 --> 00:33:33,600
- Add 20.
- Continue.

606
00:33:35,800 --> 00:33:36,400
Come on.

607
00:33:36,400 --> 00:33:38,599
Hurry up. Hurry up! Hurry!

608
00:33:38,600 --> 00:33:40,500
Da Ke will hold your legs up, okay?

609
00:33:40,500 --> 00:33:41,700
No, I'm ignoring you.

610
00:33:41,700 --> 00:33:43,299
Let me just rest for a bit.

611
00:33:43,299 --> 00:33:44,399
He's new, you should look after him.

612
00:33:44,399 --> 00:33:45,800
Help me out, okay?

613
00:33:45,800 --> 00:33:46,899
Let me rest a bit first.

614
00:33:46,900 --> 00:33:48,600
You're the captain.

615
00:33:48,600 --> 00:33:51,600
Continue. What are you doing?

616
00:33:51,600 --> 00:33:55,020
Hurry! Yes, you.

617
00:35:45,300 --> 00:35:48,800
Aren't you overtraining Xia Yu Hao?

618
00:35:48,800 --> 00:35:50,100
No.

619
00:35:50,100 --> 00:35:53,900
After running 5000 meters (3 miles), he immediately did 300 laps on a single leg in circles. Right?

620
00:35:53,900 --> 00:35:55,200
Yes.

621
00:35:56,000 --> 00:35:57,599
Then jumping rope, 500 times?

622
00:35:57,599 --> 00:35:58,300
Yes.

623
00:35:58,300 --> 00:36:01,300
Back and forth sprinting, 300 meters dash with 200 rounds?

624
00:36:01,300 --> 00:36:03,700
And after that, he still has to practice with the other members?

625
00:36:03,700 --> 00:36:05,699
It's necessary or else he won't have enough training before the competitions start.

626
00:36:05,699 --> 00:36:08,200
Aren't you being too cruel with this?

627
00:36:08,200 --> 00:36:11,300
No, we used to train like that, too. Didn't we?

628
00:36:11,300 --> 00:36:12,576
You also think it's too cruel, right?

629
00:36:12,576 --> 00:36:13,600
Me, too.

630
00:36:13,600 --> 00:36:14,500
Xuan,

631
00:36:14,501 --> 00:36:17,200
not everyone can take it like us, the geniuses.

632
00:36:17,200 --> 00:36:20,520
I agree with that sentence, but I don't think you are.

633
00:36:20,520 --> 00:36:22,500
Serve. Hurry and serve!

634
00:36:22,500 --> 00:36:23,501
Serve!

635
00:36:23,501 --> 00:36:25,300
This side. This side.

636
00:36:25,300 --> 00:36:28,200
Now just serve randomly.

637
00:36:29,100 --> 00:36:31,580
You're not catching them. You're not catching them. Hurry!

638
00:36:32,400 --> 00:36:34,900
Serve. Serve it!

639
00:36:34,900 --> 00:36:36,900
Here. Hurry, hurry, hurry!

640
00:36:36,900 --> 00:36:39,200
Hurry up! Hurry!

641
00:36:41,000 --> 00:36:42,900
Behind you.

642
00:36:42,900 --> 00:36:43,999
Underhand practice.

643
00:36:43,999 --> 00:36:45,900
Come, number one.

644
00:36:46,800 --> 00:36:48,700
Number two.

645
00:36:50,100 --> 00:36:51,900
Number three.

646
00:36:52,800 --> 00:36:53,700
Four.

647
00:36:56,900 --> 00:36:59,000
Aiyo, I didn't serve it right.

648
00:36:59,000 --> 00:37:00,100
What do you want, short legs?

649
00:37:00,100 --> 00:37:03,500
What? Newbie, hurry and practice!

650
00:37:05,400 --> 00:37:06,700
Senior, don't fight.

651
00:37:06,700 --> 00:37:08,800
Don't pull me back.

652
00:37:08,800 --> 00:37:13,000
What if he can't handle it and quits?

653
00:37:13,000 --> 00:37:15,200
We'll lose a strong player just like that.

654
00:37:15,200 --> 00:37:17,800
We'll just lose a strong player like that.

655
00:37:18,800 --> 00:37:19,700
But, Xiao Xiao,

656
00:37:19,700 --> 00:37:21,100
you can't blame me.

657
00:37:21,100 --> 00:37:23,199
He's the one in charge of the training list.

658
00:37:23,199 --> 00:37:25,400
Besides, Coach has agreed to it.

659
00:37:25,400 --> 00:37:28,600
So if you want to blame someone, you can only blame him.

660
00:37:28,600 --> 00:37:30,500
- Hey, you put me in charge of it.
- Zi Xuan!

661
00:37:30,500 --> 00:37:31,800
Senior, something's wrong!

662
00:37:31,800 --> 00:37:33,000
They are about to fight.

663
00:37:33,000 --> 00:37:34,400
- Fight?
- Who?

664
00:37:34,400 --> 00:37:35,800
Senior Jia Jun and Xia Yu Hao.

665
00:37:35,800 --> 00:37:36,601
Really?

666
00:37:36,601 --> 00:37:39,000
Yes, they are in the gym.

667
00:37:41,400 --> 00:37:42,500
You did that on purpose!

668
00:37:42,500 --> 00:37:44,300
Yes, I did it on purpose. So what?

669
00:37:44,300 --> 00:37:47,300
It annoys me to have a fool like you on our team!

670
00:37:47,300 --> 00:37:48,001
I'll help you.

671
00:37:48,001 --> 00:37:49,400
- What?
- Don't fight!

672
00:37:49,400 --> 00:37:50,900
Don't go.

673
00:37:50,900 --> 00:37:51,700
They think they can bully us because there's more of them.

674
00:37:51,700 --> 00:37:52,600
Don't cause trouble!

675
00:37:52,600 --> 00:37:53,500
I don't care!

676
00:37:53,500 --> 00:37:54,899
Come, don't you love to fight?

677
00:37:54,900 --> 00:37:56,799
You got expelled because of a fight. Hit me then!

678
00:37:56,799 --> 00:37:58,400
You--

679
00:37:59,200 --> 00:38:00,700
All of you, stop right there!

680
00:38:00,700 --> 00:38:01,500
Damn it!

681
00:38:01,500 --> 00:38:03,200
Chen Jia Jun!

682
00:38:04,100 --> 00:38:05,600
Senior.

683
00:38:05,600 --> 00:38:07,100
You, come with me.

684
00:38:07,100 --> 00:38:08,600
It had nothing to do with him.

685
00:38:08,600 --> 00:38:10,600
I wasn't talking to you.

686
00:38:12,800 --> 00:38:14,500
I'll go myself.

687
00:38:15,800 --> 00:38:17,900
What are you looking at?

688
00:38:23,200 --> 00:38:25,100
What do you think you're doing?

689
00:38:25,100 --> 00:38:27,000
It's almost competition time and you still have time to pick fights?

690
00:38:27,000 --> 00:38:28,576
Do you all have that much time

691
00:38:28,600 --> 00:38:31,000
and confidence you'll easily get to the championships?

692
00:38:31,000 --> 00:38:33,500
Raise your hand if you do!

693
00:38:36,500 --> 00:38:38,400
You punk, dared to raise your hand.

694
00:38:38,400 --> 00:38:41,200
Everyone, down for 100 push-ups.

695
00:38:41,200 --> 00:38:43,600
Jia Jun, you'll do 200.

696
00:38:43,600 --> 00:38:44,700
Xiao Xiao, you count.

697
00:38:44,700 --> 00:38:46,300
Okay.

698
00:38:46,300 --> 00:38:48,300
Come on. Hurry.

699
00:38:50,800 --> 00:38:51,899
Let's start.

700
00:38:51,900 --> 00:38:55,100
One, two...

701
00:38:56,600 --> 00:38:59,900
That short legs started it first.

702
00:38:59,900 --> 00:39:02,099
I've already said to not cause trouble while you're on the team.

703
00:39:02,099 --> 00:39:04,700
If you can't handle it, then you don't have to force yourself to stay.

704
00:39:06,000 --> 00:39:07,899
No matter how you guys make trouble for me,

705
00:39:07,899 --> 00:39:09,800
I won't leave.

706
00:39:11,400 --> 00:39:12,699
Junior,

707
00:39:12,699 --> 00:39:14,799
if you're afraid that I'm going to reveal your job,

708
00:39:14,799 --> 00:39:17,300
don't worry, I'm not that bored.

709
00:39:17,300 --> 00:39:19,100
No.

710
00:39:24,000 --> 00:39:26,100
I'm doing this for my mom.

711
00:39:26,100 --> 00:39:27,600
What?

712
00:39:46,600 --> 00:39:47,600
Are you a mama's boy?

713
00:39:47,600 --> 00:39:49,200
You're a mama's boy!

714
00:39:49,200 --> 00:39:51,100
I just...

715
00:39:51,100 --> 00:39:52,999
don't want to disappoint her anymore.

716
00:39:52,999 --> 00:39:54,800
She hopes to see me play in the competition,

717
00:39:54,800 --> 00:39:57,300
so I'll play.

718
00:39:57,300 --> 00:39:59,600
Did you think anyone on the team can get on the court?

719
00:39:59,600 --> 00:40:00,800
You can--

720
00:40:00,800 --> 00:40:01,799
I can what?

721
00:40:01,799 --> 00:40:03,099
Train me.

722
00:40:03,099 --> 00:40:04,700
Train me as a starter.

723
00:40:04,700 --> 00:40:06,399
You and He Cheng En kept pestering me,

724
00:40:06,399 --> 00:40:08,200
isn't it because I can?

725
00:40:08,200 --> 00:40:09,700
It's only because you could be one.

726
00:40:09,700 --> 00:40:11,900
Then, just make "could be" into "can be."

727
00:40:11,900 --> 00:40:13,499
What's so hard about playing volleyball?

728
00:40:13,499 --> 00:40:15,000
See?

729
00:40:17,800 --> 00:40:20,400
"What's so hard about playing volleyball?"

730
00:40:20,400 --> 00:40:21,700
Yeah.

731
00:40:23,800 --> 00:40:26,000
Do you really want to try?

732
00:40:27,000 --> 00:40:29,140
You better prepare yourself then.

733
00:40:38,700 --> 00:40:39,400
Here. Do it again.

734
00:40:39,400 --> 00:40:41,200
Set the ball overhead.

735
00:40:44,400 --> 00:40:46,560
Keep it right above your forehead.

736
00:40:56,700 --> 00:40:58,299
Put some force into your fingers.

737
00:40:58,300 --> 00:41:00,300
Soften your knees.

738
00:41:08,400 --> 00:41:10,600
Maintain it at forehead level.

739
00:41:12,700 --> 00:41:15,400
I didn't ask you to set the ball using your forehead.

740
00:41:18,900 --> 00:41:21,000
Did it hit your eye?

741
00:41:21,000 --> 00:41:22,400
Let me take a look.

